The paper deals with the complexity of Constraint Satisfaction Problems (CSPs), which is a fundamental algorithmic problem in Computer Science. The paper focuses on the "hybrid" setting of CSPs, where both sides of the problem are restricted simultaneously. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses algebraic machinery and graph theory, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the paper discusses the chromatic number of a relational structure, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO).
